\description{
An \link[R6:R6Class]{R6} class that trims the TNT tree buffer by discarding
all but the last \code{n} trees currently held in memory.

This command is a thin wrapper around the TNT \code{keep} command. Its
primary use within \pkg{nitro} is to flush the tree buffer after the
suboptimal tree sampling stage of branch support calculation, ensuring
that only the optimal trees — reloaded immediately afterwards via a
\link{ReadTreesCommand} — are present in memory when \code{bsupport} runs. This
is necessary because TNT's \code{bsupport} command compares all trees
currently in the buffer against the optimal trees to determine the
minimum score difference required to lose each group; retaining
suboptimal trees in the buffer at that point would produce incorrect
support values.
}
\details{
\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces \verb{keep <number>;}. Setting \verb{$number} to \code{0}
discards all trees currently in the buffer.
