\subsection{Queue integration}{

Unlike most command classes, \verb{$enqueue()} requires an explicit
\code{priority} argument. This is because \code{KeepTreesCommand} may need to be
inserted at different positions in the queue depending on context. When
used by \link{BranchSupportCommand}, it is enqueued at priority \code{504},
placing it after the suboptimal sampling loop (priority \code{502}--\code{503})
and before the optimal trees are reloaded (priority \code{505}).
}
